post_text:
Exeter Unified will be providing Drive Thru Breakfast & Lunch during the duration of school closures. These are offered to ALL students up to the age of 18, regardless of free or reduced meal status.

Please note: this is a drive-thru service only. We are asking that you stay in your vehicles and maintain the flow of traffic. Students receiving the meals must be present.

Who: Children 18 years and younger
What: Free Breakfast and Lunch
Days: Beginning April 20, 2020- Meals will be distributed on Mondays and Wednesdays ONLY. Students will pick up meals for 2 and 3 days at a time.
Time: 11:30 AM - 12:30 PM
Where: Elementary School Sites

Rocky Hill Elementary School
313 Sequoia Drive, Exeter, CA

Lincoln Elementary School
333 South "D" St., Exeter, CA

For additional questions, please contact our district office.

Thank you.

shared_text:
Exeter Branch Library
March 13, 2018 at 7:03 PM ·

We are excited! Exeter Branch Library has been selected as one of ten pilot library branches in California for the 2018 Developing Library Makerspaces project, a joint venture with the California State Library and the Center for Childhood Creativity at the Bay Area Discovery Museum. As a pilot project, the hope is to determine key ingredients for success in building, running, and sustaining successful makerspaces that can assist our own library system as well as all interested libraries throughout the state. This is a two-year project and the Library will receive funding for the initial start-up costs. Makerspaces provide hands-on, creative ways to encourage students to design, experiment, build and invent as they deeply engage in science, engineering and tinkering.
text:
Exeter Branch Library
March 13, 2018 at 7:03 PM ·

We are excited! Exeter Branch Library has been selected as one of ten pilot library branches in California for the 2018 Developing Library Makerspaces project, a joint venture with the California State Library and the Center for Childhood Creativity at the Bay Area Discovery Museum. As a pilot project, the hope is to determine key ingredients for success in building, running, and sustaining successful makerspaces that can assist our own library system as well as all interested libraries throughout the state. This is a two-year project and the Library will receive funding for the initial start-up costs. Makerspaces provide hands-on, creative ways to encourage students to design, experiment, build and invent as they deeply engage in science, engineering and tinkering.

Time to unite and have some fun! Let's show why we are known for our small town charm, community involvement and Monarch Pride! Only 17 days left to join in on the fun! New this year - honoring some major events in Monarch Sports Samantha Hilvers and the Lady Monarch Volleyball, Valley Champs! Join EUHS for this once-a-year community dinner event! Once again, Coach Lasky will be fixing his special slow cooked beef on Thursday, 12/7/17! Dinner will be served in the EUHS Cafeteria from 5 PM - 7PM. Each plate costs $12 and includes slow cooked beef, baked beans, rice pilaf and dessert.

EUHS is still looking for sponsors for this event. A $150 donation gets your name on the back of EUHS shirts and table advertising, and included 4 dinner tickets. For more information, contact Margie Reed at EUHS.

Take Note: School offers night classes at EUHS

The Sun-Gazette Newspaper
September 27, 2017 at 3:43 AM ·

Visalia Adult School is offering classes for high school diploma, general education degree (GED), English as a second language (ESL) and citizenship. Under an agreement with Exeter Union High School, the adult school has been allowed to use space at the high school for night classes. Childcare available for free to students enrolled in the class. Classes are held from 6 to 9 p.m. [ 52 more words ]

http://www.thesungazette.com/article/education/2017/09/27/take-note-school-offers-night-classes-at-euhs/
